data.name: DateTimeRange
desc: represents a range of date+time values.
**since**
LibreOffice 4.1

items.name: StartNanoSeconds
desc: contains the start nanoseconds (0 - 999 999 999) for the range.

items.name: StartSeconds
desc: contains the start seconds (0-59) for the range.

items.name: StartMinutes
desc: contains the start minutes (0-59) for the range.

items.name: StartHours
desc: contains the start hour (0-23) for the range.

items.name: StartDay
desc: contains the start day of month (1-31 or 0 for a void date) for the range.

items.name: StartMonth
desc: contains the start month of year (1-12 or 0 for a void date) for the range.

items.name: StartYear
desc: contains the start year for the range.

items.name: EndNanoSeconds
desc: contains the end nanoseconds (0 - 999 999 999) for the range.

items.name: EndSeconds
desc: contains the end seconds (0-59) for the range.

items.name: EndMinutes
desc: contains the end minutes (0-59) for the range.

items.name: EndHours
desc: contains the end hour (0-23) for the range.

items.name: EndDay
desc: contains the end day of month (1-31 or 0 for a void date) for the range.

items.name: EndMonth
desc: contains the end month of year (1-12 or 0 for a void date) for the range.

items.name: EndYear
desc: contains the end year for the range.

items.name: IsUTC
desc: true: time zone is UTC false: unknown time zone.
**since**
LibreOffice 4.1
